}}

Document:
{book_content}

IMPORTANT: Include ALL significant encounters (attacks, near-misses, evasions). Be as detailed as the patrol report allows. If information is not specified in the report, use null or 'Not specified'.

Identify 5-10 moments in this patrol report that would benefit from historical or technical context boxes. These will be inserted as sidebars in the published volume.

Return a JSON object with this structure:

{{
  "context_boxes": [
    {{
      "title": "The Mark 14 Torpedo Problem",
      "insertion_point": "BODY:12",
      "content_type": "Technical",
      "content": "The Mark 14 torpedo plagued US submarines in the early war years with three major defects: running too deep, faulty magnetic exploders, and weak contact exploders. By late 1943, most issues were resolved through persistent testing by submarine commanders. This patrol benefited from the improved Mark 14 Mod 3 with reliable contact exploders."
    }},
    {{
      "title": "Operation Barney: Mining the Sea of Japan",
      "insertion_point": "BODY:25",
      "content_type": "Historical",
      "content": "In June 1945, nine US submarines (the 'Hellcats') penetrated the heavily-mined Tsushima Strait to hunt in the Sea of Japan, previously considered a safe haven for Japanese shipping. This daring operation sank 28 ships totaling over 54,000 tons but cost one submarine, USS BONEFISH."
    }}
  ]
}}

Content types: Technical, Historical, Biographical, Geographic, Tactical

Examples:
- Technical: Weapons systems, submarine capabilities, equipment
- Historical: Related campaigns, strategic context, other operations
- Biographical: Notable commanders, crew members, enemy commanders
- Geographic: Strategic importance of patrol areas, base locations
- Tactical: Doctrine evolution, innovative tactics, lessons learned

Document:
{book_content}

IMPORTANT: Each content box should be 100-150 words. Choose insertion points where context enhances understanding without interrupting the narrative flow.
